Package Hospital.Argument

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    PublicArgument<T>
    This class holds the answer to some information that is needed.
    WorldPopulatedArgument
    Interface to populate information in Arguments that need it.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicArgument<T>
    A BasicArgument has a question to ask the user, the answer of which must be able to be parsed to a given type.
    BooleanArgument
    Boolean version of Public Argument, used to ask a boolean value of the user.
    CampusInfoArgument
    Campus version of an Argument, selectes a Campus from a list.
    IntegerArgument
    Integer version of Public Argument, used to ask an integer value of the user.
    ItemArgument
    This class is used to enter one or multiple comma seperated itemnames to a answer
    ListArgument<E>
    This is a Argument to select a object from a list.
    NoneArgument
    a Argument that does nothing
    PriorityArgument
    An Argument to enter the Priority of a Appointment
    StringArgument
    String version of Argument, used to ask a String of the user.
    TimeArgument
    Time version of Public Argument, used to ask a Time of the user.
    WorldArgument
    This is a private argument to give the world to the factories etc.
